---
intent: >
  Implementation plan for the SEO/discoverability infrastructure and scaffold
  tree expansion. Adds rendered pages for all aide_init artifacts (agents,
  commands, skills), updates metadata across every page, extends sitemap,
  adds llms.txt, adds CanonicalTag, and replaces the docs index with a
  scaffold-tree view.
---

## Plan

### 1. [x] Define types for scaffold artifacts and page metadata

Read:
- `coding-playbook/workflow/type-system.md`
- `coding-playbook/architecture/folder-structure.md`

Create `src/types/scaffold.ts` with:
- `ScaffoldArtifact` type: `{ slug: string; title: string; description: string; kind: "agent" | "command" | "skill"; contentHtml: string; sourceText: string; publishedAt: string }`. The `slug` is the URL segment (e.g., `aide-architect`), `title` is the display name (e.g., `AIDE Architect`), `description` is the 140-160 char meta description, `kind` discriminates the artifact category.
- `ScaffoldTreeEntry` type: `{ filename: string; slug: string; title: string; kind: "doc" | "agent" | "command" | "skill" }`. Used by the docs index scaffold tree component.
- `PageSeo` type: `{ title: string; description: string; canonicalUrl: string; ogType: "website" | "article"; jsonLd: Record<string, unknown> }`. Shared shape for per-page SEO metadata generation.

No dependencies on other steps.

---

### 2. [x] Create the scaffold artifact content service

Read:
- `coding-playbook/foundations/conventions.md` (progressive disclosure, JSDoc, naming)
- `coding-playbook/architecture/folder-structure.md` (orchestrator/helper pattern)

Create `src/service/scaffold/` with the orchestrator/helper pattern:

- `src/service/scaffold/renderArtifact/index.ts` — default export `renderArtifact({ slug, kind }): Promise<ScaffoldArtifact>`. Reads the source markdown file from disk based on kind and slug mapping (agents from `.claude/agents/aide/{slug}.md`, commands from `.claude/commands/aide/{slug}.md` or `.claude/commands/aide.md` for the root aide command, skills from `.claude/skills/{slug}/SKILL.md`). Parses the markdown into HTML using the same `renderMarkdown` helper from `src/service/docs/renderCanonical/renderMarkdown/`. Returns the full `ScaffoldArtifact`.

- `src/service/scaffold/renderArtifact/resolveSourcePath/index.ts` — default export `resolveSourcePath({ slug, kind }): string`. Maps a slug + kind to the filesystem path of the source markdown file. The slug-to-filename mapping for commands is: `aide` -> `aide.md` (at commands root), `aide-spec` -> `commands/aide/spec.md`, `aide-research` -> `commands/aide/research.md`, etc. (strip the `aide-` prefix to get the filename). Agents map directly: slug = filename. Skills: `study-playbook` -> `skills/study-playbook/SKILL.md`.

- `src/service/scaffold/listArtifacts/index.ts` — default export `listArtifacts(): ScaffoldTreeEntry[]`. Returns the complete ordered list of all scaffold artifacts for the tree view. Hardcoded — all slugs are known at build time. Returns docs (from renderHub), then agents, then commands, then skills, each in the order defined in the spec's llms.txt section.

- `src/service/scaffold/artifactMeta/index.ts` — default export `artifactMeta({ slug, kind }): PageSeo`. Returns the complete SEO metadata object for a given artifact. Contains the hardcoded title and description mappings for every artifact (the spec mandates unique, non-templated descriptions). Generates the TechArticle JSON-LD, canonical URL, and OG type. Every title follows the pattern `{Concept Name} -- AIDE: Autonomous Intent-Driven Engineering`. Every description is 140-160 chars, includes "AIDE", reads like a dictionary definition.

The `artifactMeta` helper is the single source of truth for all per-page SEO data for agents, commands, and skills. The title/description pairs are hardcoded strings, not generated from templates, per the spec's undesired outcome about near-duplicate templated descriptions.

Dependencies: Step 1 (types).

---

### 3. [x] Create the CanonicalTag client component

Read:
- `coding-playbook/client/seo.md` (canonical tag pattern for static exports)
- `coding-playbook/client/components.md` (component file structure)

Create `src/components/shared/CanonicalTag/index.tsx`. This is a `"use client"` component that:
- Reads `usePathname()` from `next/navigation`
- In a `useEffect`, injects/updates a `<link rel="canonical" href="https://aidemd.dev{pathname}">` tag in the document head
- Strips trailing slashes; uses `""` for the root path (so canonical is `https://aidemd.dev`, not `https://aidemd.dev/`)
- Returns `null` (renders nothing)

Then wire it into `src/app/layout.tsx` by importing and rendering `<CanonicalTag />` inside the `<body>` tag (it must be inside body since it's a client component using hooks). This is the confirmed pattern from the playbook for static exports — `alternates.canonical` in `generateMetadata` is unreliable with `output: "export"`.

No dependencies on other steps (can run in parallel with step 2).

---

### 4. [x] Update existing page metadata (homepage, docs hub, doc pages)

Read:
- `coding-playbook/client/seo.md` (generateMetadata, OG tags, JSON-LD)
- `coding-playbook/foundations/conventions.md` (naming)

Update three existing files to align titles, descriptions, OG tags, and JSON-LD with the spec:

**4a. `src/app/page.tsx`** — Update the `metadata` constant:
- Title: `AIDE: Autonomous Intent-Driven Engineering -- Code is ephemeral. Intent is law.`
- Description: the spec's homepage description (140-160 chars, starts with "AIDE (Autonomous Intent-Driven Engineering)...")
- OG tags: title, description, url (`https://aidemd.dev`), siteName (`AIDE`), type (`website`)

**4b. `src/app/docs/page.tsx`** — Update the `metadata` constant:
- Title: `Scaffold Tree -- AIDE: Autonomous Intent-Driven Engineering`
- Description: a unique description describing the scaffold tree index (not the old "byte-faithful" description which now belongs on individual doc pages)
- OG tags: matching title/description, url (`https://aidemd.dev/docs`), siteName (`AIDE`), type (`website`)

**4c. `src/app/docs/[slug]/page.tsx`** — Update `generateMetadata` to:
- Use title pattern `{doc.title} -- AIDE: Autonomous Intent-Driven Engineering`
- Write unique descriptions per doc. Create a `docMeta` lookup (similar to `artifactMeta` in step 2) inside a new helper `src/service/docs/docMeta/index.ts` that maps each doc slug to its specific title and description. The spec provides example descriptions for the Spec page, Progressive Disclosure page, etc. Every doc gets a unique 140-160 char description.
- Set OG type to `article`
- Add TechArticle JSON-LD to the page component (not in generateMetadata). Use `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` with a unique `id` attribute like `id="ld-doc-{slug}"`. Schema fields: headline, description, url, datePublished (from `citationMeta.publishedAt`), author (TetsuKodai Group LLC org), publisher (TetsuKodai Group LLC with url).

Dependencies: None (existing files, existing service layer).

