### 5. [x] Create agent dynamic route pages

Read:
- `coding-playbook/client/seo.md` (generateMetadata, generateStaticParams, JSON-LD)
- `coding-playbook/architecture/folder-structure.md`

Create `src/app/agents/[slug]/page.tsx`:

- `generateStaticParams()` — returns hardcoded array of all agent slugs: `aide-spec-writer`, `aide-domain-expert`, `aide-strategist`, `aide-architect`, `aide-implementor`, `aide-qa`, `aide-aligner`, `aide-auditor`, `aide-explorer`. Note: `aide-researcher` exists on disk but is NOT in the spec's artifact inventory. Exclude it unless the spec is updated.
- `generateMetadata({ params })` — calls `artifactMeta({ slug, kind: "agent" })` from step 2. Returns title, description, and openGraph (title, description, url, siteName `AIDE`, type `article`).
- Default export renders the artifact page. Calls `renderArtifact({ slug, kind: "agent" })`. Renders inside an `<article>` element with the content HTML. Includes TechArticle JSON-LD script tag with unique `id="ld-agent-{slug}"`.
- Reuse `DocLayout` and `InstallFooter` from existing components for consistent page structure.

Create a page component `src/components/ArtifactPage/index.tsx` that is shared across agent, command, and skill pages. It receives `ScaffoldArtifact` + `PageSeo` and renders:
- `<article>` wrapper
- Title as `<h1>`
- Rendered content HTML
- JSON-LD script tag
- `InstallFooter`

Dependencies: Steps 1, 2.

