### 10. [x] Create llms.txt route handler

Read:
- `coding-playbook/client/seo.md`
- `coding-playbook/architecture/folder-structure.md`

Create `src/app/llms.txt/route.ts`:

- Export `const dynamic = "force-static"` (same pattern as robots.ts and sitemap.ts).
- Default export a `GET` function that returns a `new Response(content, { headers: { "Content-Type": "text/plain" } })`.
- The content is the exact llms.txt body specified in the spec's Strategy section, with descriptions after each URL. Every agent, command, and skill entry includes a brief inline description (following ` -- `) so an LLM can answer "what does X do?" from the file alone.
- Hardcode the content string. All entries are known at build time and the spec provides the exact structure.

Dependencies: None (standalone route handler).

